ugreen-dxp-leds-dkms (0.3.1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Run lintian with the Debian profile in the Ubuntu-based publishing
    workflow.
  * Add Debian copyright metadata and package-maintainer VCS metadata.
  * Keep module autoload configuration as a dpkg-managed conffile.
  * Fix source package versioning for the native package format.
  * Improve LED class device names and sysfs output helpers.
  * Fix initial LED brightness state and cleanup on partial probe failure.
  * Align human-facing names on UGREEN DXP LED kernel module.
  * Keep repeated LED I2C binding attempts quiet when the client already
    exists.
  * Unbind the LED I2C client during package removal.
  * Remove the optional I2C bus override file on purge.
  * Fail driver probe when no LEDs are detected on an I2C client.
  * Improve I2C binding diagnostics and support an explicit I2C_BUS override.
  * Bind the LED controller I2C device from the DKMS package.
  * Install a systemd oneshot service and helper script for boot-time probing.
  * Document manual recovery when the module is loaded but LEDs are missing.
  * Refactor to proper dh-dkms packaging
  * Fix version consistency (0.3)
  * Use debhelper for automated builds
  * Change architecture to 'all' (source-only)

 -- Luca Paolini <lookap@gmail.com>  Wed, 03 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0200

